---
description: Python conventions
globs: ["**/*.py"]
---
- Python 3.12. Use modern syntax (match/case, walrus, PEP 604 unions: `int | None`).
- Type hints are mandatory on all public functions. Run mypy in strict mode.
- Use Pydantic v2 for all data contracts and config models.
- Use `pathlib.Path`, never `os.path`.
- Prefer composition over inheritance. Dataclasses or Pydantic models, not bare dicts.
- Logging: use `logging.getLogger(__name__)`, never `print` outside notebooks.
- Errors: raise specific exceptions, never bare `except:`.
- Docstrings: Google style on all public functions.
- Tests: pytest with fixtures; one test file per module under `tests/`.
- Lint/format: ruff (line length 100). No black, no isort — ruff handles both.
